# Deploy — Maryland Driveway Restore

## Actions taken

### mw-backend (2 commits)
1. `maryland_driveway_wp_bridge_blueprint.py` + `server.py` — bridge registered.
   - Commit `8bddc2a` pushed; auto-deploy restarted Flask ~30s later.
2. Gzip passthrough bug fixed — bridge was forwarding `Accept-Encoding: gzip` from browser
   to WordPress, WP responded compressed, bridge stripped `Content-Encoding` header (hop-by-hop),
   client received binary garbage. Fix: added `"accept-encoding"` to `_HOP` so upstream never
   compresses. Commit `347356a` pushed; second Flask restart confirmed.

### michaelwegter.com (1 commit, rebased)
- `src/data/workSamples.js` — id:17 `maryland-driveway-restore` entry added.
- GH Pages build: **completed / success** (run `28309630993`, 1m 4s).

