## handoff
- produced: both repos pushed and live; bridge gzip bug fixed; all 10 routes 200; GH Pages rebuilt with workSamples id:17.
- decisions: gzip fix via `accept-encoding` in hop-by-hop (prevents upstream compression, no body decoding needed); CORS header from WP is benign for iframes.
- next needs: deploy-test — run Playwright against live URLs; confirm iframe renders in AppFrame at `/work-samples/maryland-driveway-restore`; test WP admin login (admin/admin@123 or demo-user); verify sticky CTAs, before/after slider, pricing, gallery lightbox, FAQ accordion, and estimate form submission all function.
- risks: CORS allow-origin shows `http://localhost:3000` (WP misconfigured origin); safe for iframe nav but any JS fetch from michaelwegter.com to the bridge would be blocked — deploy-test should note if AppFrame makes fetch calls; Docker container is single point of failure but registered in services.json (auto-restart).
